<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20437/107.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-02"><hi rend="italic">July 2,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>German Government agrees to conference, but owing to absence of officials
                            representing interests of Prussian Government, could not have meeting
                            until August or September.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>